TITLE: Using the edit Method for Visual Code Editing
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the edit method which provides a more visual way to define code transitions using helper functions like replace, insert, and remove within a template string.
SOURCE: https://github.com/redotvideo/docs/blob/main/src/content/motion-canvas/code-animations.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
export default makeScene2D(function* (view) {
  const code = createRef<Code>();

  view.add(
    // prettier-ignore
    ,
  );

  yield* code().code.edit(0.6)`\
function example() {
  ${insert(`// This is a comment
  `)}console.log("${replace('Hello!', 'Goodbye!')}")
${remove(`  return 7;
`)}}`;

  yield* waitFor(0.6);
});
```

