TITLE: Contrasting Yielded Promises and Frame Generation in Revideo (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the difference between yielding a promise (like `view.add` with an image) which awaits the operation without rendering a frame immediately, and yielding multiple empty values (using a loop or `waitFor`) which explicitly generates multiple frames over time.
SOURCE: https://github.com/redotvideo/docs/blob/main/docs-old/docs/guide/understanding-scene-flow.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
yield view.add(<Img src={'img.png'} />); // yielded promise, we await it and dont render a frame.

// we yield 30 empty values, corresponding to 30 frames (or 1 second of video in case of 30fps). This is the same as calling yield* waitFor(1);
for (let i = 0; i < 30; i++) {
  yield;
}
```

