TITLE: Exporting Multiple Node References from Custom Component using `makeRef` (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how a custom function component (`Label`) can accept an object (`refs`) via props and use `makeRef` internally to populate that object with references to its child nodes (`Rect`, `Txt`). This allows the component user to access and animate specific parts of the component (`label.rect`, `label.text`).
SOURCE: https://github.com/redotvideo/docs/blob/main/docs-old/docs/motion-canvas/references.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
function Label({
  refs,
  children,
}: {
  refs: {rect: Rect; text: Txt};
  children: string;
}) {
  return (
    // highlight-next-line
    <Rect ref={makeRef(refs, 'rect')}>
      // highlight-next-line
      <Txt ref={makeRef(refs, 'text')}>{children}</Txt>
    </Rect>
  );
}

const label = {rect: null as Rect, text: null as Txt};
view.add(<Label refs={label}>HELLO</Label>);

// we can now animate both the Rect and the Text of our label:
yield * label.rect.opacity(2, 0.3);
yield * label.text.fontSize(24, 0.3);
```

