TITLE: Defining Types for Custom Component Refs (Redundancy Example) (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: Highlights a redundancy issue when using custom components that export refs (like the `Label` component). The type structure for the `refs` object (`{rect: Rect; text: Txt}`) needs to be defined both in the component's props and when creating the external `label` object.
