TITLE: Creating Reactive Children using a Spawner Function in Revideo (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the reactive approach using a 'spawner' function. By wrapping the child generation logic in a function `() => ...`, the children within the `Layout` will automatically update whenever the `count` signal changes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/redotvideo/docs/blob/main/docs-old/docs/motion-canvas/spawners.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
const count = createSignal(10);

view.add(
  <Layout layout>
    {() => range(count()).map(() => <Circle size={32} fill={'white'} />)}
  </Layout>,
);
```

